{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt all military families from school fines \u2014 let them be with family.",
        "additional_details": "We believe that it is unjust that armed forces members sacrifice their safety and family life, often living apart even outside deployment, yet face restrictions on time together when they return. A strong relationship with a serving parent is vital for a child\u2019s wellbeing. \u201cExceptional circumstances\u201d are not guaranteed and remain at a headteacher\u2019s discretion. A government that relies on the commitment and sacrifice of its armed forces should not then dictate when those same families are permitted to reunite.",
        "background": "We call on the government to exempt military families from school attendance fines. Military parents often live away from home and are deployed for weeks or months at a time. These families make extraordinary sacrifices. They deserve flexibility and compassion when spending precious time together.",
